</div>&nbsp;<h2>Blog Post With Excerpts &amp; Thumbnail Image</h2><p>If you use an excerpt &amp; assign a thumbnail image to the post, Native will automatically put the thumbnail in a circle and center it above the title. It's a great feature that can dramatically change the look of your blog just by including a new behavior in your workflow.<br></p>
  
      <img src="http://static1.squarespace.com/static/501c8d6b24ac0a1285ed8244/t/501c8d6b24ac0a1285ed8270/1342815346604/Screen+Shot+2012-07-20+at+4.07.07+PM.png?format=original" alt=""/>
  


  
