      <title>"Take Them For What They Are"</title>
      <link>/blog/2012/8/take-them-for-what-they-are</link>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Maurice Sendak, in <a href="http://www.brainpickings.org/index.php/2012/05/09/grim-colberty-tales-maurice-sendak/">what would fatefully become</a> his last public interview before he died:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>COLBERT: What’s the best thing a parent can do for a child?</p>
  
  <p>SENDAK: Love him, or her.</p>
  
  <p>COLBERT: What does that mean?</p>
  
  <p>SENDAK: Take them for what they are.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I have to admit, I subconsciously knew this was one of the last things he said publicly, but it didn't really sink in until Lori Pickert <a href="http://www.whiteoakschool.com/camp-creek-blog/2012/5/10/take-them-for-what-they-are.html">pointed it out</a>. It's honestly just too perfect for words – and so befitting the man and his legacy.</p>]]></content:encoded>
