    <item>
      <title>Children Banned from Playing in the Street</title>
      <link>/blog/2012/8/housing-estate-bans-children-from-playing-in-the-street</link>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A story from Plymouth, UK:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Residents living in Seven Trees Court received a letter from Westcountry Housing on Wednesday informing them that children are not to play on the estate. </p>
  
  <p>But Westcountry Housing said that it was "unfair" to call it a ban and claimed it was more about "parent responsibility".</p>
  
  <p>The letter said: "I am receiving complaints concerning children playing football, riding bikes/scooters, and skateboards on the Greenbank Estate which is causing a nuisance to residents. Please can you ensure that your children do not play football, ride bikes/scooters or skateboard in the parking areas or in the pedestrian areas around Albertha Close/Seven Trees Court. They should be using the grass area to play on."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Sigh. <em>Shakes head.</em></p>]]></content:encoded>
